VI for good or bad has made us a gimp constant damage dealer, but a good quick damage dealer.  I have constantly heard about wizards burning down an add quickly to help a group.  By modifying this AA to do double dam for double mana (or whatever the ratio is)... it does not increase our long term damage, but significantly boosts our short term damage. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=midgetgod>Midget God</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 369<br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/20/03 5:25 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fixes for Manburn +more </span><hr size=1> uhh, wizards are sorta tied with rogues for constant dmg output. Some are better some are not. And we are the masters of quick damage. <p>[63 Sorcerer] <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=69194">Zuratuli</a> (Gnome)<br><font size="1">"It has been a source of great pain to me to have met with so many among [my] opponents who had not the liberality to distinguish between political and social opposition; who transferred at once to the person, the hatred they bore to his political opinions." <b>- Thomas Jefferson to Richard M. Johnson</b>, 1808.</font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=splynt>Splynt</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 52<br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/24/03 6:01 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fixes for Manburn +more </span><hr size=1> I think the 3x and 4x is too far out there. I do like the idea of manaburn for the same 5 aa's (prereq MC3) that would make the next spell you cast cost 2.5X the mana and 2 times the damage then add focus (normal crit ability, based on crit aa's) and adds an extra -100 resist check to the spell with same aggro as original spell. Ideally it will scale with the Wizard so that will get better as you increase in level and gain better spells. <br>
<br>
So basically it would be: <br>
(SpellDamage *2) + (Focus%*(SpellDamage*2)) = Normal <br>
(SpellDamage *2 *2) + (Focus%*(SpellDamage*2)) = AA Crit w/scf3 <br>
<br>
Max MB (not sure on max focus so guessing ~30%) would be with SoS: <br>
Normal: (2700*2) + .30(2700*2) = 7020 damage for 1600 mana -110 resist check fire <br>
Crit: (2700*4) + .30(2700*2) = 12420 damage for 1600 mana -110 resist check fire <br>
<br>
Normal Level 60 with Sunstrike: <br>
Normal: (1615*2) + .20(1615*2) = 3876 damage for 1125 mana -110 resist check fire <br>
Crit: (1615*4) + .20(1615*2) = 7106 damage for 1125 mana -110 resist check for fire <br>
<br>
Advantages: <br>
+Doesn't use up all mana <br>
+Has -100 resist adjustment <br>
+Does 2X damage that is focusable <br>
+Possible to Crit doing 4X damage plus focus(though focus only applied to 2X the Damage) <br>
<br>
Now the limitations: <br>
-Make it reusable every 60 minutes (possible to reduce with further AA's) <br>
-Stuns the wizard for 30 Secs after the cast. <br>
-The spell won't have the unresistable effect of the old mana burn (has additional -100 resist check though). <br>
-Costs 2.5 times original mana cost of spell. <br>
-Won't reach the same high damage levels of original Manaburn Crits, will be able to surpass the new gimped mana burn in some cases (when this crits). <br>
-Will have aggro component equivalent to the original spell, not no aggro like the original manaburn. <br>
<br>
