<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=346414" target="new">The Cremster's Profile.</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=orocular>Orocular</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 67<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/1/03 11:21 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fixes for Manburn +more </span><hr size=1> Well, in response to a few posts here. <br>
<br>
Kunark dragons - Who cares? They are no longer the high end content of the game. Put a level limit on them as you did Vox and Nagafen, problem solved.<br>
<br>
The restriction to percentage of life on a mob - 25% is about right. Even if you have 100 wizards ready to MB at 25% health on the emporer, you STILL have to deal with the other 75% health of the mob. That takes tanking power. No wizard will be able to kill te emp at 25% anyways even if they crit for 24k. That is somewhat a viable solution to the MB punishment (we all know it wasn't a nerf, VI intended to punish us all for the actions of a few).<br>
<br>
Another possible solution... keep the one minute timer, however make the multiplier close to 5x mana. So if you have 5k mana mana, you do close to 25k damage. There would obviously be no percentage limit on the mob, The drawback, have the argo multiplier also at 5x as well, thus, the wizard will die, and possibly screw up the raid. You take your chances.<br>
<br>
Another idea, and my final offer. Keep the damage and timer simalar to know. However reduce the timer to 15 seconds. 15 seconds is more than ample to keep the raid concept in game.<br>
<br>
If I recall, a group of wizards on Fennin Ro DID kill Sontalak without manaburn... just to piss off VI. My point being, the wizard can do it with or without manaburn. So make the skill worth our while. In any non trivial encounter, manaburn is not going to make the difference, however could be a benefit, the way it was intended.<br>
<br>
I feel the last option is the propper solution. It keeps everything balanced while maintaining a useful skill. Even if you have 100 wizards you still have to deal with agro control in that case. <br>
<br>
JMHO <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><br>
